  if (!parseResult.success) {
    return parseResult;
  }

  return actionRegistry.executeAction(parseResult.action.verb, {
    ...context,
    action: parseResult.action
  });
}
</antArtifact>

Key aspects of this design:

1. Action System Structure:
- `ActionRegistry` manages both standard and custom actions
- Custom handlers can override standard ones
- Asynchronous execution for flexibility
- Type-safe context and results

2. Standard Library:
- Base implementations for common actions
- Consistent error handling and validation
- Effect system for tracking changes
- Reusable helper functions

3. Custom Override Support:
- Stories can override any standard action
- Can add completely new actions
- Can extend standard behavior
- Can maintain access to standard implementations

4. Effect System:
- Actions can produce multiple effects
- Effects are typed and structured
- Useful for UI updates, achievements, etc.
- Makes it easier to track game state changes

